Media notes: Other species: American Robin, House Wren.
Observation Details: New yardbird #110, and a real surprise.  Male, singing sporadically.  Dark eyemask and throat, white cheek and supercilium stripes, golden crown, large golden wing patch on greenish-gray wings, gray back and flanks, white belly and undertail.  No indication of Blue-wing hybridization.  (This bird has been looked for but not seen since Sunday May 6.  It likely moved on that night.)
